<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 21,
                            1890</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Mizner reports to Mr. Blaine that upon our demand for the restoration of
                        the arms the Guatemalan Government requires the official who seized the arms
                        on the <hi rend="italic">Colima</hi> to return them, with a written apology
                        for his act. He adds advice of the reservation of all rights for
                        damages.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>